Section P CTAN Edition

Welcome to the XML based and XSL generated version of The TeX Catalogue Online, Section P CTAN Edition. This is a listing of entries in the TeX Catalogue and may take a little time to load, but is hopefully worth it. Have a look at the Catalogue Preface for alternative ways of accessing the catalogue.

The TeX Catalogue Online is also available from any CTAN node or mirror, including the following. Pick one that is close to you. (The "search" link attempts to find a CTAN node that may be close to you, courtesy of Randy Kobes. Multiple clicks may find alternatives.)

Icons associated with many entries in the catalogue allow you to:

  • view the directory on CTAN
  • view documentation (possibly many)
  • view documentation in PDF format (requires the acroread plugin)
  • jump to the package's home page
  • download a gzip'd tar file from a nearby CTAN node (not supported by all nodes)
  • download a gzip'd tar file from ftp.dante.de

Other icons simply provide further information about the package:

  • part of the teTeX distribution
  • available on the TeX Live CD ROM

The license type, version (if known), and the date of the last change made to each particular Catalogue entry are also provided.

pkfind No caption.
The TDS standard specifies that pk and gf files contain \special strings to identify the contents of pk and gf files. Pkfind is a variant of the GNU find utility modified to understand those specials, and to act on them in some cases. For example, it can be used to delete all pk files created by gsftopk from a subdirectory tree.

psfont No caption.
Intended as a replacement for psfonts of psnfss , psfont uses one file for redefining all default fonts instead of one file for each font. It also contains all parts of psfonts.dtx which are not covered by this general concept (i.e., the pifonts, mathptm and two fd-files for Adobe Symbol and Adobe Zapf Dingbats). This file is specific to PostScript fonts. See also psfonts psnfss
license: gpl (1999/03/03)
psfonts PostScript fonts for use with TeX and LaTeX.
license: unknown (1997/05/13)
psfrag No caption.
Allows LaTeX constructions (equations, picture environments, etc.) to be precisely superimposed over Encapsulated PostScript figures, using your own favorite drawing tool to create an EPS figure and placing simple text ``tags'' where each replacement is to be placed, with PSfrag automatically removing these tags from the figure and replacing them with a user specified LaTeX construction, properly aligned, scaled, and/or rotated.
license: dfsg version: 3.04 (1998/06/24)
psizzl A TeX format from SLAC.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
pslatex Use PostScript fonts by default.
A small package that makes LaTeX default to `standard' PostScript fonts. It is basically a merger of the times and mathptm styles from the psnfss suite of packages. You must have installed standard LaTeX and the psnfss PostScript fonts to use this package. The main novel feature is that the pslatex package tries to compensate for the visual differences between the Adobe fonts by scaling Helvetica by 90\%, and `condensing' Courier (i.e. scaling horizontally) by 85\%. The package is supplied with a (unix) shell file for a `pslatex' command that allows standard LaTeX documents to be processed, without needing to edit the file.
license: lppl (1999/04/12)
psmerge No caption.
Concatenate PostScript files as long as they have been generated by the same program (e.g., generated by dvips ).
license: unknown (1996/11/1)
psnfss No caption.
Font definition files, macros and font metrics for common PostScript fonts.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
psnfssx No caption.
Extra styles and encodings for PS fonts, including Y&Y encoding support.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
pspicture PostScript picture support.
Replacement for core LaTeX picture macros to use PostScript \special commands.
license: lppl (1999/04/12)
pstoedit Translate PostScript and PDF to other formats.
Other formats include tgif, FrameMaker mif, XFig's fig, pdf, gnuplot, MS-Windows wmf, CAD exchange format dxf, LightWave 3D lwo, RenderMan rib, Real3D rib, Java applet, and Idraw format.
license: unknown version: 2.60 (1999/03/30)
pstotext Extract ASCII from PostScript and PDF.
A free Unix program that extracts ASCII text from PostScript and PDF (Acrobat) files. pstotext uses GhostScript , but does a more careful job with kerned characters and nonstandard font encodings than Ghostscript's ps2ascii utility.
license: dfsg (1996/10/31)
pstricks No caption.
An extensive collection of PostScript macros that is compatible with most TeX macro packages, including Plain TeX, LaTeX, AMS-TeX, and AMS-LaTeX. Included are macros for color, graphics, pie charts, rotation, trees and overlays. It has many special features, including: a wide variety of graphics (picture drawing) macros, with a flexible interface and with color support. There are macros for coloring or shading the cells of tables. See also color colortab fancybox shading
license: unknown (1996/05/30)
psutils No caption.
Utilities for manipulating PostScript documents, including page selection and rearrangement, resizing the page, arrangement into signatures for booklet printing, and page merging for n-up printing. Utilities include psbook, psselect, pstops, psnup, psresize, epsffit.
license: unknown (1 Apr 1991)

Donald Knuth's punk font
